highlights.text: Taylor Swift has the most spots on Top Songs USA. “Fortnight (feat. Post Malone)” is the highest at #12.
“Pink Skies” by Zach Bryan is the highest new entry on Top Songs USA at #8.
“Wind Up Missin’ You” by Tucker Wetmore is the biggest gainer on Top Songs USA, up 52 spots at #79.
“No Role Modelz” by J. Cole has been on Top Songs USA the longest, at 210 weeks straight.
